@KeithE.Truesdell Storage has some level of effect; for example, an open container vs a closed container will change the levels of vitalization and thus the rate of degradation, but its not a large effect. 

Roast makes a difference. Burnt coffee, where the oil is brought to the surface will stale much faster. Flavored coffee, where the flavorings are on the surface of the bean will likewise stale much faster. 

Very light roast coffees can often last up to a month in a nitrogen flushed vacuum pack.
